message.content: All lit up. Full of people moving as you went past." Suddenly he crouched forward. "Broughton, if I thought there were anything in Peel's Regulations to cover this I’d have you court-martialled. But I know there isn't," he added scathely. "I tried to read the registration number, sir," but it was getting dark," he wailed. But his commanding officer appeared to have forgotten him.
